properties.Title: Heat Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A period of hot weather continues. Daytime high temperatures near 30 degrees Celsius will continue again on Friday. Overnight low temperatures tonight near 18 degrees Celsius will provide little relief from the heat. Cooler temperatures with showers or thunderstorms are expected to arrive Friday evening. Please refer to your public forecast for further details on expected temperatures. Hot and humid air can also bring deteriorating air quality and can result in the Air Quality Health Index approaching the high risk category. ### The risks are greater for young children, pregnant women, older adults, people with chronic illnesses and people working or exercising outdoors. Watch for the effects of heat illness: swelling, rash, cramps, fainting, heat exhaustion, heat stroke and the worsening of some health conditions. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ONStorm.

properties.Title: Flood Warning Issued For The Churchill River From The Saskatchewan-Manitoba Border To Leaf Rapids Manitoba
properties.Summary:
Description: This is a Manitoba Emergency Alert. Manitoba Infrastructure’s Hydrologic Forecast Centre has issued a Flood Warning for the Churchill River from the Saskatchewan-Manitoba Border to Leaf Rapids Manitoba. If you are in the affected area, be watchful as local waterways are expected to rise quickly and may cause flooding. Do not attempt to cross fast flowing waters or waters of unknown depth. Use caution when driving on all roads as road conditions may have changed. Avoid flooded areas. Follow all directions by local authorities and take all necessary precautions to stay safe. Stay tuned to local media for updates. Up to date information is available at www.gov.mb.ca/flooding and www.manitoba511.ca
